<dl id="n12093m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12093m">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12093m"> 93(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Remember <font color="green">[th]</font><font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>, maid<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> thou art but / powder <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12093m"><li>FW 440.26f </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n12093m">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n12093m">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12093m">MS BL 47482b-48v</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:098 <a name="qA3d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA3d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qA3d.htm#n12093m">Draft: III&sect;2A.3</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Le seul cadeau que le fianc&eacute; fasse &agrave; sa future femme (&agrave; part l&apos;anneau de noce que seul elle porte) est un manteau de deuil, en &eacute;toffe noire avec un capuchon, c&apos;est pour le cas o&ugrave; il y aurait des d&eacute;c&egrave;s dans la famille. Il est &agrave; remarquer que seules les femmes mari&eacute;es quand elles sont en deuil, portent ces manteaux. <br><font color="green">[The only present that the groom gives his future wife (apart from the wedding ring that only she will wear) is <mark>a robe of mourning</mark>, in black linen and with a hood, for use when there has been a death in the family. It is interesting that only married women wear these mourning robes.]</font> <small> Paul-Yves S&eacute;billot, <a name="RDTP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RDTP"><cite title="source">Traditions et coutumes de Basse Bretagne</cite></a> (1904) 353</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
